cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper deals with video prediction and interpolation, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of unsupervised latent structure inference and temporal prediction also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions appearance changes due to lighting, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the use of landmarks for predictable motion interpolation suggests a possible connection to robotics (cs.RO).
